12
00:01:37.165 --> 00:01:39.695
[Frank Reciting Hebrew Prayer]

13
00:02:02.990 --> 00:02:06.330
We were slaves to Pharaoh
in the land of Egypt.

14
00:02:06.394 --> 00:02:08.764
and the Lord our God
took us out from there

15
00:02:08.829 --> 00:02:12.199
with a strong hand
and an outstretched arm.

16
00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:15.900
Uncle Frank. who's Pharaoh?

17
00:02:17.289 --> 00:02:22.509
Uh. the Pharaoh was a ruler and...

18
00:02:22.576 --> 00:02:24.306
a tyrant.

19
00:02:25.173 --> 00:02:27.108
Are our rulers tyrants?

20
00:02:27.606 --> 00:02:29.445
LAURA: It's not safe here. Frank.

21
00:02:31.219 --> 00:02:33.919
[Clatter]

22
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:36.217
- [Hissing]
- Shh.

23
00:02:36.224 --> 00:02:37.964
[Hissing Continues]

24
00:02:38.025 --> 00:02:39.285
Laura?

25
00:02:40.761 --> 00:02:42.601
[Hissing Becomes Louder]

26
00:02:46.634 --> 00:02:50.674
[Stammering] No. no. no no!

27
00:02:50.738 --> 00:02:52.668
- Uncle Frank!
- No. no. no!

28
00:02:54.242 --> 00:02:55.842
Don't breathe! Hold your breath! No!

29
00:02:55.909 --> 00:02:57.629
- John. Emily. don't breathe!
- Uncle Frank!

30
00:02:57.645 --> 00:03:00.445
No! No! Don't... Don't breathe!

31
00:03:00.514 --> 00:03:02.784
Don't breathe! Don't breathe!

32
00:05:18.752 --> 00:05:19.752
Well?

33
00:05:26.193 --> 00:05:27.863
Well what?

34
00:05:28.714 --> 00:05:29.928
What do you think?

35
00:05:34.635 --> 00:05:38.905
I think you don't really
want to know what I think.

36
00:05:39.777 --> 00:05:41.712
I mean. no offense. but
you're not the only white guy

37
00:05:41.775 --> 00:05:43.992
who wants a girl to look like a Pon.

38
00:05:44.978 --> 00:05:46.512
I'm not like those men.

39
00:05:47.915 --> 00:05:49.115
Right.

40
00:05:53.421 --> 00:05:58.761
Why don't you just tell me
what you want me to do?

41
00:06:00.428 --> 00:06:01.628
Um...

42
00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:08.500
Uh. I... I would like you
to say Gokigen-yoh.

43
00:06:11.539 --> 00:06:13.069
Goki-gen-yoh.

44
00:06:14.141 --> 00:06:15.711
Danna-sama-wa.

45
00:06:15.776 --> 00:06:19.146
I-ki-na-o-hi-to. désukoto.

46
00:06:21.749 --> 00:06:25.119
Danna-sama-wa. I-ki-wa...

47
00:06:25.185 --> 00:06:26.485
I-ki-na.

48
00:06:26.554 --> 00:06:29.964
I-ki-na-o-hi-to. deskotu.

49
00:06:30.023 --> 00:06:31.363
Désukoto.

50
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:33.989
All right. uh. again. please.

51
00:06:34.061 --> 00:06:40.101
Danna-sama-wa. I-kina-
o-hi-to. désukoto.

52
00:06:40.635 --> 00:06:42.105
Danna-sama-wa.

53
00:06:42.618 --> 00:06:46.042
I-ki-na-o-hi-to. désukoto.

54
00:06:49.083 --> 00:06:51.136
You have no idea
what you're saying. do you?

55
00:06:51.723 --> 00:06:52.723
Does it matter?

56
00:06:53.363 --> 00:06:55.020
It's dirty talk. right?

57
00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:00.685
Once again. And this time. just...

58
00:07:02.407 --> 00:07:03.959
with real feeling.

59
00:07:07.632 --> 00:07:10.246
_

60
00:07:10.247 --> 00:07:12.247
_

61
00:07:13.365 --> 00:07:15.365
_

62
00:07:58.712 --> 00:08:00.312
Are the cufflinks finished?

63
00:08:01.059 --> 00:08:02.180
Yes.

64
00:08:03.018 --> 00:08:05.119
I just need to polish them.

65
00:08:05.323 --> 00:08:06.815
Well. get a move on.

66
00:08:07.386 --> 00:08:10.117
Everything must be
absolutely "pafekuto."

67
00:08:10.711 --> 00:08:11.711
Mm-hmm.

68
00:08:13.392 --> 00:08:14.561
You do know what today is.

69
00:08:15.103 --> 00:08:16.103
Of course I do.

70
00:08:16.952 --> 00:08:18.003
Have you seen Frank?

71
00:08:18.065 --> 00:08:19.565
No. I have not.

72
00:08:45.392 --> 00:08:47.932
You're welcome to join me. Mr. Frink.

73
00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:53.370
No thanks. I don't. uh...

74
00:08:53.433 --> 00:08:54.903
Fair enough.

75
00:09:03.677 --> 00:09:05.077
I'm Hagan.

76
00:09:05.145 --> 00:09:06.375
Reverend.

77
00:09:06.446 --> 00:09:08.076
I saw you at Karen's service.

78
00:09:08.148 --> 00:09:11.178
- I'm not a Reverend anymore.
- Right. No.

79
00:09:11.251 --> 00:09:13.951
Now you're... a what?

80
00:09:14.021 --> 00:09:15.021
A fighter.

81
00:09:16.277 --> 00:09:17.989
How does that sit with God?

82
00:09:18.083 --> 00:09:20.717
The problem with promising
people their reward in heaven

83
00:09:20.717 --> 00:09:24.336
is they're liable to sit
on their asses here on Earth.

84
00:09:24.337 --> 00:09:30.001
eating shit and hoping they'll
sprout wings real soon.

85
00:09:30.964 --> 00:09:32.340
That's why I didn't mind so much

86
00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:34.335
when they de-frocked us.

87
00:09:35.315 --> 00:09:39.207
You know. I thought
Jesus might approve of that.

88
00:09:39.729 --> 00:09:41.528
He didn't need a dog collar

89
00:09:41.576 --> 00:09:43.789
to make people sit up and take notice.

90
00:09:45.405 --> 00:09:47.392
What about turning the other cheek?

91
00:09:48.117 --> 00:09:50.064
Christ was no pacifist.

92
00:09:50.917 --> 00:09:53.893
He lived in a suffering society. too.

93
00:09:54.261 --> 00:09:57.201
That old King James translation?

94
00:09:57.647 --> 00:09:59.288
Resist all evil?

95
00:09:59.351 --> 00:10:02.268
Bullshit propaganda. my friend.

96
00:10:02.335 --> 00:10:03.995
- Amen to that.
- Amen.

97
00:10:04.567 --> 00:10:06.371
Hagan. here. showed me the path. Frank.

98
00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:09.939
He'll show you too.
if you care to listen.

99
00:10:10.811 --> 00:10:12.611
Thanks for coming. brother.

100
00:10:13.414 --> 00:10:14.414
What's going on?

101
00:10:14.710 --> 00:10:15.987
I asked you here

102
00:10:16.026 --> 00:10:19.119
because that explosive
you recovered for us?

103
00:10:20.721 --> 00:10:21.821
We're going to use it.

104
00:10:22.364 --> 00:10:23.536
Hagan: We're going to divide it up

105
00:10:23.537 --> 00:10:24.733
to make smaller bombs.

106
00:10:25.169 --> 00:10:27.377
then we're going to use
them to assassinate

107
00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:29.764
the top ranking Pons
in the Pacific States.

108
00:10:30.238 --> 00:10:32.870
Hit the bastards where it hurts.

109
00:10:33.366 --> 00:10:35.073
There's a big-deal Pon general in town.

110
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:37.135
Thanks to you. we can take him out

111
00:10:37.204 --> 00:10:38.844
without sacrificing any of our people.

112
00:10:39.686 --> 00:10:41.336
And you want my help to make the bomb.

113
00:10:41.408 --> 00:10:42.808
No. I want you and Sara

114
00:10:42.876 --> 00:10:44.236
to figure out where to place it.

115
00:10:44.311 --> 00:10:46.111
Hagan's people have been
tracking the general.

116
00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:47.676
They think they've found a pattern.

117
00:10:47.748 --> 00:10:49.678
He goes to the same place.
same time every day.

118
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:51.390
You'll watch his route
when he gets there.

119
00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:54.248
work out the best place
to plant the explosive.

120
00:10:56.206 --> 00:10:57.616
What about reprisals?

121
00:10:58.413 --> 00:10:59.785
They'll get worse.

122
00:11:15.075 --> 00:11:16.075
Okay.

123
00:11:17.077 --> 00:11:18.077
GARY: Good.

124
00:11:20.981 --> 00:11:22.951
You know. if this is just a dry run.

125
00:11:23.016 --> 00:11:24.416
I can always go on my own.

126
00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:29.460
That won't work.

127
00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:30.992
Uh...

128
00:11:31.058 --> 00:11:33.888
just do as you're told. Okay. brother?

129
00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:38.230
Yeah.

130
00:11:40.768 --> 00:11:43.338
Pervitin to help with fatigue.

131
00:11:43.403 --> 00:11:44.673
Obetrol for my figure.

132
00:11:44.772 --> 00:11:46.272
Eukadol for my muscle pain.

133
00:11:46.339 --> 00:11:48.639
and of course cocaine for my sinuses.

134
00:11:48.776 --> 00:11:50.036
[Sigh]

135
00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:53.080
I'm going to miss Dr. Adler. We all are.

136
00:11:53.146 --> 00:11:54.246
You should really consider

137
00:11:54.314 --> 00:11:56.424
snagging yourself a doctor. Julia.

138
00:11:57.117 --> 00:11:58.453
To keep you in prescriptions?

139
00:11:58.518 --> 00:12:02.288
[Giggle] Well. that's
what friends are for.

140
00:12:02.714 --> 00:12:04.214
How's it going in here?

141
00:12:04.412 --> 00:12:06.794
Glad to see our refugee
is earning her keep.

142
00:12:06.860 --> 00:12:10.860
Here. this will help oil
the wheels of industry.

143
00:12:13.176 --> 00:12:16.935
Um. you know. actually.
I should probably get going.

144
00:12:18.619 --> 00:12:20.419
You mean to say
you dressed for a funeral.

145
00:12:20.462 --> 00:12:22.243
but you didn't intend to actually go?

146
00:12:22.309 --> 00:12:23.309
I wasn't invited.

147
00:12:23.376 --> 00:12:25.276
I just offered to help
Lucy with the flowers.

148
00:12:25.345 --> 00:12:27.845
and thought I should
dress appropriately.

149
00:12:27.915 --> 00:12:29.815
Well. of course you should come.

150
00:12:30.410 --> 00:12:31.823
I'm just teasing.

151
00:12:31.852 --> 00:12:34.922
I'm sure there will be an eligible M.D.
or two for you to meet.

152
00:12:35.856 --> 00:12:38.026
We're going for poor Alice.

153
00:12:49.736 --> 00:12:51.496
Tohru?

154
00:12:51.571 --> 00:12:56.547
_

